name: integer_u32_u16_maximum
description: |
  This is u16 maximum represented as u32. It is the last value that
  survives narrowing to u16; the paired next value requires bit 16
  and exposes truncation, masking, and arithmetic performed at the wrong width.
format: hex
decode-as: u32
pair:
  - with: ../u16/maximum.input
    hint: equal
  - with: above-u16-maximum.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u32"
  - "lower-width"
  - "maximum"
  - "boundary"
  - "narrowing"
  - "truncation"
---
ff ff 00 00   # 65535
